{{about||the engineering plastic|Polyoxymethylene|the flavor compound|1,1-Diethoxyethane{{!}}1,1-diethoxyethane}}
{{distinguish|acetyl}}
[[File:Acetal general structure.svg|thumb|Generic structure of acetals]]
An '''acetal''' is a [[functional group]] with the connectivity R<sub>2</sub>C(OR')<sub>2</sub>). Here, the R groups can be organic fragments (a carbon atom, with arbitrary other atoms attached to that) or [[hydrogen]], while the R' groups must be organic fragments not hydrogen. The two R' groups can be equivalent to each other (a \symmetric acetal\") or not (a \"mixed acetal\"). Acetals are formed from and convertible to [[aldehyde]]s or [[ketone]]s and have the same [[oxidation state]] at the central carbon

